observations.recommendation:
We recommended to the Local Chief Executive the following:
Direct the requisitioning office to prepare and submit the RIS to the GSO for consolidation of all inventories issued by the GSO;
Require the GSO to prepare and submit SSMI based on the consolidated RIS submitted by the requisitioning office and to submit the same to the office of the Municipal Accountant to support the recognize inventory expenses;
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to recognize the inventory expenses based on the submitted SSMI by the GSO; and
Require the Inventory Committee to submit Report of the Physical Count of Inventories (RPCI) to the Auditor not later than July 31 and January 31 of each year for the first and second semesters, respectively.

We recommended to the Local Chief Executive to enjoin the following department heads’ compliance with the requirements in COA Circular 2015-008:
Direct the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant, General Services Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects;
Require the Municipal Accountant the following reporting procedures:
-	Prepare the Journal Voucher (JV) to record the beginning balance of the local road network and its components in the general ledger and the Local Road Network Ledger Card, respectively;
-	Support the JV with the Registry of Public Infrastructures for Roads, working paper on the distribution of costs for the road components, and working paper on the determination of the depreciated replacement cost for road components with no available cost per registry;
-	Keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network; and
-	Prepare a lapsing schedule for the computation of the depreciation for each component at the end of the year; and
Direct the General Services Officer-Designate to maintain the Local Road Inventory and Road Map, and to keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components.

a. Direct the Municipal Engineer to conduct an inventory of all municipal road networks and provide the GSO and the Accountant a copy thereof;

b. Direct the General Services Officer (GSO) to maintain the Local Road Network Property Card (LRNPC) for each road network and to report the same in the proper format using the Report on the Physical Count of Local Road Networks where the different road components are detailed and road network ID number is indicated; and

c. Direct the OIC-Municipal Accountant to create and maintain a Local Road Network Ledger Card (LRNLC) for each local road network and to identify the unrecorded Road Networks.

a. Direct the Municipal Treasurer to institute a system such as E-Tracs that could facilitate the prompt determination, assessment, and collection of real property tax;

b. Direct the Municipal Treasurer to intensify the collection of Real Property Taxes and to give emphasis on the collection of the delinquent real property taxes by applying the administrative remedies against delinquent taxpayers as provided for under the Local Government Code;

c. Direct the Municipal Treasurer to give emphasis on the collection of the delinquent real property taxes by applying the administrative remedies against delinquent taxpayers as provided for under the Local Government Code;

d.  Hire additional employee assigned in the office of the assessor, otherwise, require the concerned employee to render overtime in order to prepare and submit the estimated real property tax collectibles; and

e. Direct the Municipal Accountant Designate to record Tax Receivables at the beginning of the year.

