Direct the General Service Officer and the Municipal Accountant to record the PPEs that has no documents or records by using the fair market value;
Direct the General Services Officer to maintain the Stock Cards for inventories and the Property Cards for PPEs and incorporate the balances in the Report on the Physical Count of Inventories (RPCI) and Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE); and
Direct the Municipal Accountant to update the Supplies Ledger Card (SLC) and Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Card (PPELC) and reconcile the balance against the Report on the Physical Count of Inventories (RPCI) and Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE).

We recommended to the Local Chief Executive to require the General Services Officer to:
Issue property tags/ stickers for each PPE in order to identify and trace the location of the said PPEs;
Issue corresponding Acknowledgement Receipt for Equipment (ARE) for all the Properties, Plant and Equipment issued to officials and employees who have the custody thereof;
Assign additional competent personnel to complete the needed property records;
Renew the Acknowledgement Receipt for Equipment (ARE) every January of the third year after issuance; and
Strictly comply with the provisions of Section 259 of GAM Vol. I for LGU for the succeeding procurement and issuances of Properties, Plant and Equipment.

Recommendations:
We recommended to the Local Chief Executive to:
a.) 	Create an Inventory Committee to include Department Head to conduct the complete and latest physical inventory count of all PPE and submit Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE);
b.) 	Designate the General Services Officer as head of the Inventory Committee;
c.) 	Direct the Inventory Committee to check the condition of the PPE and prepare the Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP) and Waste Materials Report (WMR) for the damaged, obsolete and unserviceable PPE identified in the course of inventory-taking and request for its immediate disposal.
d.) 	Instruct the General Services Officer-Designate/ Supply Officer and the Acting Municipal Accountant to regularly reconcile their records and review the composition of the PPE account to come up with an accurate Property, Plant and Equipment account balance.

We have recommended the following:

a.) The Municipal Accountant to prepare and submit Bank Reconciliation Statements monthly in adherence to Section 74 of PD 1445 and COA Circular No. 96-11. Also require her to get the monthly bank statements from the depository bank promptly and regularly;

b.) The Municipal Accountant to prepare an adjusting entries for the staled checks, prepare a letter immediately to the concerned bank for the discrepancies found in the bank statements, maintain subsidiary ledger for each collectors, and prioritize the verification of other recurring reconciling items to bring the cash in bank account in its correct balance;

c.) The Municipal Treasurer to reconcile her cashbooks entries with that from the accounting records at least quarterly; and

d.) The Collecting Officers to submit the Report of Collections and Deposits to the accounting division individually.

e.) Request the Local Chief Executive and the Municipal Treasurer to enroll in LBP i-access so that bank balances can be viewed and printed anytime.
